  "url": "PR5.html#remark-estimating-max-and-min-values",
  "type": "Remark",
  "number": "4.5.16",
  "title": "",
  "body": "  We can estimate where these local maxima and minima occur by looking at other characteristics, such as multiplicities and end behavior.  From , we saw that when the function touches the -axis at a zero, then that zero could be either a local maximum or a local minimum of the graph. When the function crosses the -axis, however, the local maximum or local minimum occurs between the zeros.   "
